## Why This Is Asked
Tests ability to apply practical logging security to prevent token leakage in fintech contexts, a common attack surface.

## Key Concepts
- Log data leakage risks
- Redaction and sanitization
- Middleware for request/response logs
- CI gates for secrets in code
- Incident response and key rotation

## Code Example
```javascript
function redactLog(obj){
  const redacted = JSON.parse(JSON.stringify(obj), (k,v)=>{
    if (/token|secret|api_key|Authorization/i.test(k)) return "[REDACTED]";
    return v;
  });
  return JSON.stringify(redacted);
}
```

## Follow-up Questions
- How would you test the redaction effectively?
- How would you handle binary payloads or proprietary log formats?
- What logging libraries and CI tools would you choose and why?

## Why This Is Asked

